  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Develop national education policy and planning capacities to ensure quality lifelong learning opportunities for all in South Asia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNESCO NDL will support countries in the cluster to mainstream the SDG 4 targets and initiatives in their national education policies and plans, to align policy making with assessment outcomes. Special attention will be given to inclusion and learning for all especially girls and women and the integration of SDG4 target 4.2 relative to ECCE in the perspective of development of lifelong learning systems. In doing so, the office will actively promote a rights-based approach to education as well as UNESCO&apos;s 1960 Convention on against Discrimination in Education. 
In partnership with UNESCO HQ/offices/institutes, direct technical support will be provided to the selected countries in the Cluster and the SAARC framework for Education 2030 will be supported through a monitoring mechanism.</narrative>
  </description>
